# Portable Build Only

- When the user asks to build or package the Windows desktop app, use the portable build flow by default.
- Prefer `pnpm run tauri:build:portable` for the full portable app bundle.
- Use `pnpm run tauri:build:portable:runtime` only when the portable runtime itself needs to be refreshed separately.
- Do not run `pnpm run tauri:build` or produce MSI/installer bundles unless the user explicitly asks for a non-portable build.
- If a previous non-portable build was started by mistake, stop it and switch to the portable flow.
